
Que 3)  Multi-Channel Payment System with Offers
================================================

Problem Statement:
You are developing a Multi-Channel Payment System for an e-commerce platform.
The system supports different payment methods:
Credit Card
Debit Card
UPI

Each payment type:
Processes payment differently
Applies different discount offers
Returns a final payment message

To maintain flexibility and scalability, implement the system using:

Spring Core (Annotation-based)
Factory Design Pattern using Map-based Injection ONLY

The system should dynamically select the correct payment service at runtime.

Requirements:
=============

1️) Create interface Payment
String pay(double amount);

2️) Create implementation classes:
CreditCardPayment
DebitCardPayment
UPIPayment

Special Conditions (Important Twist):
Each class must:
Be annotated with @Component
Use names:
"credit"
"debit"
"upi"

-> Discount Logic:
Credit Card → 10% discount
Debit Card → 5% discount
UPI → 15% discount

-> Final Amount Formula:
Final Amount = Amount − (Amount × Discount)

-> Output Format:
"Paid <finalAmount> using Credit Card"
"Paid <finalAmount> using Debit Card"
"Paid <finalAmount> using UPI"

3️) Create Factory class PaymentFactory
Conditions:
Annotate with @Component
Use Map injection:
@Autowired
private Map<String, Payment> paymentMap;

Method:
public Payment getPayment(String type)
Logic:
Convert type to lowercase
Fetch from map
If not found → throw exception

4️) Create Configuration class
@Configuration
@ComponentScan(basePackages = "your package name")

5️) Create Main class (ELC)

Class Name: PaymentApp

Responsibilities:
Load Spring container
Take input:
Payment type
Amount
Get object using factory
Call pay(amount)
Print result
Handle invalid input

Sample Input/Output:
--------------------
Enter payment type: upi
Enter amount: 1000
Paid 850.0 using UPI

